/* THE TESTIMONY (the knowing-together): kyma's laws in the one tongue --
 * the Born rule was SELECTED by basis-invariance (arm 240, Parseval); the
 * classical bound 2 sits strictly under the Tsirelson value (arm 239, both
 * emerged by complete enumeration, gap decided by the exact sign oracle);
 * the contextual square admits no valuation (arm 241, Kochen-Specker,
 * 512-enumeration zero); the global phase is carried inside the exact
 * amplitude (Y = zeta^2 X Z, first-class). */
fn ky_testify() -> u64 @export {
    return "[born_rule = basis_invariance] [classical_bound 2 < tsirelson_value] [contextual_square = no_valuation] [global_phase < exact_amplitude]" as u64
}

